208
00:10:53,310 --> 00:10:56,230
So I want to talk about
two main concepts when

209
00:10:56,230 --> 00:10:57,410
you're connecting your data.

210
00:10:57,410 --> 00:10:59,350
Because most
likely, you're going

211
00:10:59,350 --> 00:11:02,590
to have to connect
multiple sources together.

212
00:11:02,590 --> 00:11:06,450
And Tableau has two
primary routes for this.

213
00:11:06,450 --> 00:11:09,710
The main route is relationships.

214
00:11:09,710 --> 00:11:13,550
And relationships are
rather new to Tableau

215
00:11:13,550 --> 00:11:18,230
as a way to simplify and
create more efficiencies

216
00:11:18,230 --> 00:11:20,130
within the application.

217
00:11:20,130 --> 00:11:23,550
But relationships are
a dynamic, flexible way

218
00:11:23,550 --> 00:11:27,550
to combine data from
multiple tables for analysis.

219
00:11:27,550 --> 00:11:30,730
You don't define join
types for relationships.

220
00:11:30,730 --> 00:11:33,310
So you won't see the
traditional Venn diagram

221
00:11:33,310 --> 00:11:34,950
when you create them.

222
00:11:34,950 --> 00:11:37,470
Here are just four
bullet points as to why

223
00:11:37,470 --> 00:11:40,230
relationships work in Tableau.

224
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:42,550
It just makes your
data source easier

225
00:11:42,550 --> 00:11:44,890
to define, change, and re-use.

226
00:11:44,890 --> 00:11:45,850
Trust me on this.

227
00:11:45,850 --> 00:11:50,200
And you'll see this as we bring
in different data sources.

228
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,960
It also makes it
easier to analyze

229
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:56,140
data across multiple tables at
the correct level of detail.

230
00:11:56,140 --> 00:11:58,920
That's what LOD stands
for, Level Of Detail.

231
00:11:58,920 --> 00:12:02,040
It does not require the
use of LOD expressions

232
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:06,020
or LOD calculations for analysis
at different levels of detail.

233
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:08,180
Again, that's probably
an advanced use,

234
00:12:08,180 --> 00:12:10,160
but it does simplify
the process.

235
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:14,360
And then only query data
from tables with fields

236
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:16,060
used in the current viz.

237
00:12:16,060 --> 00:12:20,680
So it really helps
allow the analyst

238
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:26,960
to access the tables without
streamlining them and creating

239
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:28,260
one single table.

240
00:12:28,260 --> 00:12:32,480
So that's good news,
because they're making

241
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:34,580
our life a little bit easier.

242
00:12:34,580 --> 00:12:36,800
So let's go ahead and
go back to this orders

243
